subject: Re: [junit] Re: equals is "commutative" ... so
msgSnippet: ... There is no such thing, by definition, not in logic, not in mathematics, not anywhere. Equals are equal. Commutativity is implied. J. B. Rainsberger,
messageBody:
>So said Thomas SMETS on 2003-05-20 --------------------
>
>Fine but I really feel equals should behave so.
>The question is more do you have a need for NON-commutative equals.

There is no such thing, by definition, not in logic, not in mathematics, not anywhere. Equals are equal. Commutativity is implied.
